A lot of the questions about "how realistic should this be?" are very dependent on the question "How did anthros come to exist in this universe?".

If they developed humanoid bodies naturally through convergent evolution then it'd seem sensible for them to be a bit more realistic.
If it's a "wizard did it" kind of situation then you have carte blanche to just make whatever is the most appealing.
Radioactive mutants/science experiment gone wrong type scenarios present a bit more of a middle ground.
